convertFitsFormatToJavaType

public static int convertFitsFormatToJavaType(java.lang.String format,
                                              boolean asciiTable)
Returns the numerical code of the Java type matching the FITS column format FITS Array cells are not considered Bits are considered as Strings Complex are also considered as Strings (but not supported by Java FITS!!) The response is noty the same to ASCII or BINARY table. ASCII have less supported types.

Parameters:
format -
asciiTable - : true if the considered table is an ASCII table
Returns:
